import torch
from TTS.api import TTS

# Get device
device = "cuda" if torch.cuda.is_available() else "cpu"

# List available üê∏TTS models
print(TTS().list_models())

# Init TTS
tts = TTS("tts_models/multilingual/multi-dataset/xtts_v2").to(device)

# Run TTS
# ‚ùó Since this model is multi-lingual voice cloning model, we must set the target speaker_wav and language
# Text to speech list of amplitude values as output
#wav = tts.tts(text="Hello world!", speaker_wav="output.wav", language="en")
# Text to speech to a file
txt = """
We gather today not just as individuals, but as a community united by a shared purpose. Look around you. Each person here holds a unique talent, a different perspective, and a story that has brought them to this very moment. It's the mosaic of our diverse strengths that forms the foundation of our collective success.
Let's not forget that the greatest achievements are born from collaboration, from the willingness to lift each other up, and from the courage to learn from our failures. The path forward will have its challenges, but it's in those moments that our resilience is forged and our true character is revealed."""
tts.tts_to_file(text=txt, speaker_wav="output.wav", language="en", file_path="output_sample.wav")